# No Blocking I/O on the World Transaction Goroutine

In Dragonfly, callbacks passed to `EntityHandle.ExecWorld(...)` and the `Run`
methods of `cmd.Command` execute on the **world's transaction goroutine**.
Anything blocking that runs there freezes world ticks for every player and
has been observed to surface runtime crashes inside `net/http`.

## The rule

Inside any of the following contexts, do **not** call HTTP clients, sleep,
wait on channels, hold long mutexes, or do disk I/O:

- `handle.ExecWorld(func(tx *world.Tx, e world.Entity) { ... })`
- `cmd.Command.Run(src, output, *world.Tx)`
- `world.Tx`-receiving callbacks generally

## Pattern: fetch first, apply via ExecWorld

When you need both data from a player **and** an HTTP/disk call:

```go
// ❌ BAD - HTTP call blocks the world transaction goroutine
handle.ExecWorld(func(_ *world.Tx, e world.Entity) {
    p := e.(*player.Player)
    resp, err := moderation.GlobalService().InflictionOfPlayer(p) // blocks!
    // ...apply state...
})
```

```go
// ✅ GOOD - capture cheaply, do I/O off-thread, re-enter ExecWorld to apply
var xuid string
handle.ExecWorld(func(_ *world.Tx, e world.Entity) {
    if p, ok := e.(*player.Player); ok {
        xuid = p.XUID()
    }
})
if xuid == "" {
    return
}

resp, err := moderation.GlobalService().InflictionOfXUID(xuid)
if err != nil || resp == nil {
    return
}

handle.ExecWorld(func(_ *world.Tx, e world.Entity) {
    p, ok := e.(*player.Player)
    if !ok {
        return
    }
    // apply resp to p
})
```

## Pattern: command Run methods

`cmd.Command.Run` runs on the transaction goroutine. Disconnect / mutate the
victim inline, but fire HTTP sync to external services from a goroutine.

```go
// ❌ BAD
func (k Kick) Run(src cmd.Source, o *cmd.Output, _ *world.Tx) {
    moderation.GlobalService().AddInfliction(...) // blocks the tx goroutine
    victim.Disconnect(...)
}

// ✅ GOOD
func (k Kick) Run(src cmd.Source, o *cmd.Output, _ *world.Tx) {
    name := victim.Name()
    go func() {
        if err := moderation.GlobalService().AddInfliction(...); err != nil {
            slog.Default().Error("kick sync failed", "target", name, "error", err)
        }
    }()
    victim.Disconnect(...)
}
```

## Reference implementations

- `pokebedrock/session/ranks.go` (`rankWorker`) — HTTP runs on the worker
  goroutine; `ExecWorld` is used only for popups, messages, and `SetNameTag`.
- `pokebedrock/session/inflictions.go` (`processInflictionRequest`) — captures
  XUID via `ExecWorld`, performs HTTP off-thread, re-enters `ExecWorld` to
  apply effects.
